cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.DB, cs.CV, cs.DS

The paper deals with efficient processing of nearest neighbor queries on high-dimensional multimedia data, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR), multimedia (MM), and database (DB) systems. The proposed technique also involves strategies for optimizing query processing, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) and data structures (DS). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR, cs.MM, and cs.DB, followed by cs.CV and cs.DS.
